        "client_msg_id": "85a1c8f8-3322-4cd6-adf4-519d10f73ceb",
        "text": "We received the 3i CTLS, I am very impressed with it, especially considering it is an ex-demo system and has been around the block more than a few times.\n\nPros:\n• Mounting is simple (bondic glue, or clamp from two sides) and the sample holder sits very nicely in place with magnets.\n• Extremely easy to find the sample using a pre-scan and then a 3D pre-scan to work out the extents of the lateral tiling you should do. \n• Setting up multiple channels is intuitive, just tick or untick the boxes\n• Easy post-objective zoom module to change sampling of pixels without doing any objective changes \n• Only need to change objective when going to really high resolution (sub 1-micron)\n• Works with many imaging mediums\n• No dipping of objectives in any medium, less cleaning\n• Can easily view the sample at any time with your eyes (this is said coming from a Leica DLS, where it is impossible to see the sample - we have a black box around the scope)\n• Software is easy for making quick movies, downsampling options, testing merges before doing the final one\n• Can export as other file types if needed, also able to load the native .sldy files in bioformats for e.g. ImageJ\nCons:\n• Software is a little buggy when it comes to prescan and positioning of the final acquisition, i.e. define it in one place, but it starts imaging in another - they are aware and are very open to feedback and making changes. NOTE: this doesn't always happen\n• Open-top reservoir is a little prone to spillage\n• Glass coverslip sits on top of reservoir and if you get medium on it, it needs cleaning, which takes time and can be frustrating\n• Need to re-calibrate the SLM every time you want to acquire images at a different zoom or refractive index. I.e. there is no way to save these files for each combo and just load up a previous file from a previous SLM calibration - they will work on this, I'm sure\n• No user config files saved for the software, so can't save settings for an acquisition to return to the next day\nThere are probably more, happy to show it\/talk about it to anyone who wants to see it, by Zoom or in person.",
        "team": "T01FQQGKPLH",
        "user_team": "T01FQQGKPLH",
        "source_team": "T01FQQGKPLH",
        "user_profile": {
